Steps to create Spring boot project:
    1. Spring starter project
        java, maven, 17
    2. Select the dependency
        ex: when we want to interact with database:
                . Spring Data JPA
                . MySQL Driver
    3. Fill the properties file
        We have to add url, username, pwd, drivers, etc that are required to connect to the DB.
        Since we have added datajpa and mysql dependency, so spring boot will try to auto configure database connection
    4. Package creation
        com.cts -------------- Base Package (because it has @SpringBootApplication)
        com.cts.entity ------- It has model class for our project
            Ex: Customer/Product/User
            These classes should be encapsulated (i.e declare variables as private and use public setters, getters)
            Each entity represents a table in the DB
            Always creae a default(required) & parameterized constructor(based on need) -> This is to follow the conventions
        com.cts.repository
            In springboot application, if we use spring data jpa, then this layer become complete abstraction
            Just define the interface, at runtime spring data jpa will provide the implementation
        com.cts.service
            We write the business logic
            Create a service interface and then provide the implementation
        com.cts.controller
    
@Entity
    Marks a class as a DB table

@Id
    Marks the variable(field) as primary key

These 2 are mandatory annotations for Entity classes

